<div class="service">
  <p><b>Location</b> : Its a geographical location where Azure datacentre exists. There are around 10 locations spreaded across the globe.</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"name" => "North Europe", "available_services" => "Compute, Storage, PersistentVMRole, HighMemory"}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>Affinity Group</b> : Its a logical group created within a specified location to keep your services more nearer to each other. Associated cloud and storage services should be placed within an affinity group to minimize network latency. It is a logical name for a colocated set of compute and storage nodes.</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"name" => "groupname", "label" => "customlabel", "description" => "description", "location" => "Location.objs.to_s", "hosted_services" => "?", "storage_services" => "", "capabitlity" => "Compute, Storage"}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>Cloud Service</b> : When you create an application and run it in Azure, the code and configuration together are called an Azure cloud service</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"url" => "https://management.core.windows.net/<subscription-id>/services/hostedservices/<cloudservicename>", "name" => "cloudservicename", "label" => "cloudservicename", "description" => "", "location" => "", "affinity_group" => "", "status" => "Created", "date_created" => "", "date_modified" => "", "extended_properties" => {"ResourceGroup"=>"test-cservice", "ResourceLocation"=>"Southeast Asia"}, "default_winrm_certificate_thumbprint" => "", "virtual_machines" => {}, "deployment_name" => ""}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>StorageAccount</b> : Azure Storage includes three services: Blob storage, Table storage, and Queue storage. These services are included in every storage account. A storage account provides your unique namespace for working with blobs, queues, and tables. It also stores the VHDs for virtual machine & OS.</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"url" => "https://management.core.windows.net/subscription_id/services/storageservices/storage_account_name", "name" => "storage_account_name", "description" => "custom_desc.", "location" => "location-name", "affinity_group" => "affinity-group-name", "label" => "custom-label", "status" => "Created", "endpoints" => ["http://testinng.blob.core.windows.net/", "http://testinng.queue.core.windows.net/", "http://testinng.table.core.windows.net/"], "geo_replication_enabled" => "true", "geo_primary_region" => "Southeast Asia", "status_of_primary" => "Available", "last_geo_failover_time" => "", "geo_secondary_region" => "East Asia", "status_of_secondary" => "Available", "creation_time" => "2014-11-10T06:19:34Z", "extended_properties" => [{:name =>"ResourceGroup", :value=>"Default-Storage-SoutheastAsia"}, {:name=>"ResourceLocation", :value=>"Southeast Asia"}]}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>Container</b> : Its a container created inside a Storage which can further contain Blobs, Queues, Tables. Its analogus to Amazon S3's Bucket</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"name" => "groupname", "properties" => {"last_modified" => "Fri, 07 Nov 2014 11:49:46 GMT", "etag" => "\"0x8D1C8980FE400E3\"", "lease_status" => "unlocked", "lease_state" => "available"}, "meta_data" => {}, "public_access_level" => ""}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>Blob</b> : Its used to store files, images, audio, video, unstructured data. It can be accessed under Storage > Container. Its 2 types are "Block BLOBs" & "Page BLOBs". Block blobs are optimized for streaming. Page blobs are optimized for random read/write operations and which provide the ability to write to a range of bytes in a blob. Any blob can be leased for exclusive write access. When a blob is leased, only calls that include the current lease ID can modify the blob or (for block blobs) its blocks.</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"name" => "user-given-name", "snapshot" => "", "properties" => {:last_modified=>"Mon, 10 Nov 2014 07:36:45 GMT", :etag=>"0x8D1CAD036705ADE", :lease_status=>"unlocked", :lease_state=>"available", :content_length=>12799, :content_type=>"application/octet-stream", :content_encoding=>"ASCII-8BIT", :content_language=>"", :content_md5=>"JRYzmXDXEIGVhfkHc66+Cg==", :cache_control=>"", :blob_type=>"BlockBlob"}, "metadata" => {}}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>Queue</b> : Azure Queue storage is a service for storing large numbers of messages that can be accessed from anywhere in the world via authenticated calls using HTTP or HTTPS. A single queue message can be up to 64 KB in size, and a queue can contain millions of messages, up to the total capacity limit of a storage account. It can be accessed under Storage > Container</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"name" => "qu-name", "url" => "http://<storage-name>.queue.core.windows.net/<qu-name>", "metadata" => {}}) %></pre>
</div>

<div class="service">
  <p><b>Table</b> : The Azure Table storage service stores large amounts of structured data. The service is a NoSQL datastore which accepts authenticated calls from inside and outside the Azure cloud. Azure tables are ideal for storing structured, non-relational data.</p>
  <p><b>Entity</b> : Analogus to column of a table</p>
  <pre class="code"><%= JSON.pretty_generate({"properties" => {"PartitionKey"=>"test-partition-key", "RowKey"=>"1", "Timestamp"=> "2014-11-12 07:50:12 UTC" }, "table" => "table-name", "etag" => "", "updated_at" => "2014-11-12 08:22:29 UTC"}) %></pre>
  <p><b>Batch</b> : A collection of commands for a table which needs to be executed in bulk</p>
</div>

